    "services.ai.page.title": "Computer Vision &",
    "services.ai.page.titleAccent": "ML",
    "services.ai.page.description": "Vision and machine learning where physical work happens: production lines, robotic cells, document flows. Inspection systems that catch defects humans miss, vision pipelines that guide robots in real time, and OCR that turns industrial paperwork into structured data the rest of your stack can use.",
    "services.ai.inspection.title": "Industrial Inspection & Defect Detection",
    "services.ai.inspection.description": "Camera-based inspection on production lines: surface defects, missing parts, misaligned components, dimensional checks, presence and orientation verification. Trained on your parts and your lighting, deployed at the line with pass/fail signals into the PLC and rich data into the historian. Adjacent uses: package and label inspection in logistics, crop and livestock monitoring in agriculture, infrastructure inspection from drones or fixed cameras.",
    "services.ai.vgr.title": "Vision-Guided Robotics & Automation",
    "services.ai.vgr.description": "Vision pipelines that tell robots and machines where to act: pick-and-place from bins or conveyors, pose estimation, bin picking, palletizing with mixed SKUs, machine tending, quality-driven sorting. Tight coupling between the camera, the model, and the PLC or robot controller, with cycle times that match the line.",
    "services.ai.ocr.title": "OCR, Barcodes & Industrial Document Understanding",
    "services.ai.ocr.description": "Reading 1D barcodes (Code 128, GS1-128, EAN), 2D codes (Data Matrix, QR), DPM-marked parts, plus printed and handwritten paperwork: work orders, labels, traceability tags, invoices, delivery notes, certificates. Layout-aware extraction goes beyond raw text to structured fields with validation rules, confidence scoring, and human review queues for the cases the model isn't sure about. Output flows straight into ERP, MES, WMS, or your data lake.",
