    "services.ai.faq.q1": "How long does a typical industrial AI project take?",
    "services.ai.faq.a1": "A vision proof of concept on a single station or line usually takes 2-4 weeks. Production-ready systems with PLC integration, edge deployment, and operator UI typically take 2-6 months, depending on data availability and how clean the existing process is.",
    "services.ai.faq.q2": "Do we need a large dataset to get started?",
    "services.ai.faq.a2": "Not always. For visual inspection we often start with a few hundred labeled images using transfer learning, then expand the dataset as the line runs. When data is missing entirely, we set up the capture pipeline first (cameras, lighting, storage) and start collecting before training.",
    "services.ai.faq.q3": "Can the models run on the edge, near the machine?",
    "services.ai.faq.a3": "Yes. We deploy on industrial PCs, NVIDIA Jetson, or compact edge devices next to the line for low-latency inference. The cloud is used for training, monitoring, and rollups, but inference stays close to the equipment.",
    "services.ai.faq.q4": "How do the models talk to PLCs and SCADA?",
    "services.ai.faq.a4": "We expose results over OPC UA, MQTT, Modbus, or REST, depending on what the control system speaks. A pass/fail signal can drive a reject actuator directly; richer data goes to the SCADA, MES, or historian alongside the rest of the production data.",
    "services.ai.faq.q5": "What happens when the product or process changes?",
    "services.ai.faq.a5": "Models drift when SKUs, suppliers, lighting, or layouts change. We build retraining and labeling tools so your team can adapt the model without us, and offer ongoing support packages where we own the retraining cycle.",
